    <!-- CATERING CTA -->

    <section>
      <div class="flex">
        <div class="w-[65%]">
          <img
            src="/catering-taco-project.webp"
            alt="Catering"
            class="w-full h-auto object-cover"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="w-[35%] bg-sky">
          <div
            class="px-6"
            style="width: calc(var(--max-content-width) * 0.35);"
          >
            <h2
              class="text-ocean font-futura text-[96px] font-[950] leading-[88%] tracking-[-4.8px] uppercase"
              style="text-wrap:balance;"
            >
              We'll Come to You
            </h2>
            <div class="bottom-wrapper">
              <div
                class="text-ocean font-holiday text-[48px] font-normal leading-[130%] rotate-[-4deg]"
              >
                We cater!
              </div>
              <p
                class="font-geist text-ink text-[14px] leading-[1.4] lowercase"
              >
                Whether you're hosting a corporate event, birthday party, or
                family gathering, The Taco Project makes it easy. Choose from
                our curated catering packages or build your own taco bar. We
                provide everything you need—from fresh ingredients to serving
                utensils—so you can focus on enjoying delicious tacos with all
                the provided fixings.
              </p>
              <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
                <h2
                  class="font-futura text-ocean text-[56px] leading-[0.9] uppercase tracking-[-2.8px]"
                >
                  catering
                </h2>
                <a
                  href="#"
                  class="flex items-center gap-2 text-ocean font-geist text-[14px] uppercase hover:opacity-80 transition-opacity"
                >
                  details
                  <svg
                    xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                    viewBox="0 0 12.427 12.427"
                    class="size-[12.427px]"
                  >
                    <path
                      fill="currentColor"
                      d="M3.5 3.5h5.427v5.427"
                      stroke="currentColor"
                      stroke-width="1.5"
                      stroke-linecap="round"
                      stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
                    <path
                      fill="none"
                      stroke="currentColor"
                      stroke-width="1.5"
                      stroke-linecap="round"
                      d="M8.927 3.5L3.5 8.927"></path>
                  </svg>
                </a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Stress Free Catering Section -->
      <section class="bg-crema py-[100px] px-5 overflow-hidden">
        <div class="max-w-[1150px] mx-auto relative">
          <div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row gap-20">
            <!-- Left Content -->
            <div class="flex-1 flex flex-col gap-8">
              <h2
                class="font-futura text-citrus text-[64px] lg:text-[96px] leading-[0.88] uppercase tracking-tight"
              >
                stress-free<br />catering
              </h2>
              <p
                class="font-geist text-ink text-[14px] leading-[1.4] max-w-[440px]"
              >
                From our Build-Your-Own Taco Bar to boxed lunches to beverages,
                we've got you covered. Oh - and don't forget the guacamole.
                Contact us to customize your taco party packages for guests of
                all ages!
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Right Content - Event Types -->
            <div class="flex-1 relative mt-10 lg:mt-0">
              <p
                class="font-holiday text-ink text-[40px] leading-none whitespace-nowrap -rotate-4 mb-4"
              >
                We cater a variety of event types
              </p>

              <ul
                class="font-futura text-citrus text-[40px] leading-none tracking-tight list-none space-y-2"
              >
                <li class="mb-0">Corporate Lunches</li>
                <li class="mb-0">Anniversary Parties</li>
                <li class="mb-0">Fundraiser Dinners</li>
                <li class="mb-0">Birthday Parties</li>
                <li class="mb-0">Game Night</li>
                <li class="mb-0">Company Picnics</li>
                <li class="mb-0">Holiday Gatherings</li>
                <li class="mb-0">Graduations</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div
            class="font-holiday text-citrus text-[64px] font-normal -rotate-4 ms-36"
          >
            How it Works
          </div>

          <div class="max-w-[1150px] mx-auto mt-8">
            <!-- Steps -->
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
              <!-- Step 1 -->
              <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
                <div class="aspect-[1/1] w-full overflow-hidden">
                  <img
                    src="/catering-guest-list.webp"
                    alt="Prepare the Guest List"
                    class="w-full h-full object-cover"
                    loading="lazy"
                    decode="async"
                  />
                </div>
                <h3
                  class="font-futura text-citrus text-[32px] leading-none tracking-tight"
                >
                  Prepare the Guest List
                </h3>
                <p class="font-geist text-ink text-[14px] leading-[1.4]">
                  We'll need to know: when, and how many. And if there are any
                  allergies or dietary restrictions, let's note those, too.
                </p>
              </div>
              <!-- Step 2 -->
              <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
                <div class="aspect-[1/1] w-full overflow-hidden">
                  <img
                    src="catering-ordering.webp"
                    alt="Order Online"
                    class="w-full h-full object-cover"
                    loading="lazy"
                    decode="async"
                  />
                </div>
                <h3
                  class="font-futura text-citrus text-[32px] leading-none tracking-tight"
                >
                  Order your Package
                </h3>
                <p class="font-geist text-ink text-[14px] leading-[1.4]">
                  We offer two convenient packages with all the proteins, all
                  the fixins, and utensils if you need them. Add on drinks,
                  desserts, and more.
                </p>
              </div>
              <!-- Step 3 -->
              <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
                <div class="aspect-[1/1] w-full overflow-hidden">
                  <img
                    src="catering-enjoy.webp"
                    alt="Enjoy your delicious taco bar"
                    class="w-full h-full object-cover"
                    loading="lazy"
                    decode="async"
                  />
                </div>
                <h3
                  class="font-futura text-citrus text-[32px] leading-none tracking-tight"
                >
                  Enjoy!
                </h3>
                <p class="font-geist text-ink text-[14px] leading-[1.4]">
                  Swing by the location you ordered from and pick up your order:
                  portioned, hot, and ready to serve.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Catering FAQ Section -->
        <section class="flex flex-col md:flex-row">
          <!-- On Ordering -->
          <div
            class="flex-1 bg-peach py-[80px] px-5 flex flex-col items-center gap-10 border-r border-ink/10"
          >
            <h2
              class="font-futura text-ink text-[40px] uppercase tracking-[-2px] leading-[0.92]"
            >
              on Ordering
            </h2>
            <div
              class="w-full max-w-[512px] flex flex-col border-t border-ink"
              id="ordering-faq"
            >
              {
                [
                  {
                    q: "Is there a minimum order for catering?",
                    a: "Yes. 10 people.",
                  },
                  {
                    q: "How many tacos will I get per person with my order?",
                    a: "Our Taco Packages accommodate three soft tortilla tacos per person. We also offer hard shells, if you would like hard shells, please notate this on your order or mention it when speaking with a catering representative.",
                  },
                  {
                    q: "How far in advance should I order?",
                    a: "A 24-hour advance is ideal, but please call the store if your order is last minute and we will always do our best to accommodate your needs.",
                  },
                  {
                    q: "Do you offer alcohol?",
                    a: "Yes, we do. We have a great selection of wine, beer, margaritas and sangria.",
                  },
                  {
                    q: "Is gratuity included in my bill?",
                    a: "No. Please feel free to leave gratuity separately to our amazing team!",
                  },
                  {
                    q: "Who do I contact if I have any questions about my order or need to make a change?",
                    a: "Please call the store you ordered from directly.",
                  },
                  {
                    q: "Can I make up my own menu or make changes to your menu?",
                    a: "Our chefs are specifically trained to our own menu, so unfortunately we cannot accommodate requests outside of what we currently offer.",
                  },
                  {
                    q: "What is your Cancellation/Refund Policy?",
                    a: "Orders cancelled within 24 hours of your pick up time will be fully refunded. If cancelled less than 24 hours, you will be charged 1/2 your bill.",
                  },
                ].map((faq, index) => (
                  <div class="border-b border-ink">
                    <button
                      class="faq-toggle flex items-center justify-between gap-4 py-5 px-10 text-left w-full hover:bg-black/5 transition-colors cursor-pointer group"
                      aria-expanded="false"
                      aria-controls={`faq-answer-${index}`}
                    >
                      <span class="font-geist text-ink text-[16px] leading-[1.4]">
                        {faq.q}
                      </span>
                      <svg
                        xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                        fill="none"
                        viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                        stroke-width="1.5"
                        stroke="currentColor"
                        class="size-4 text-ink shrink-0 transition-transform duration-200 group-aria-expanded:rotate-180"
                      >
                        <path
                          stroke-linecap="round"
                          stroke-linejoin="round"
                          d="M19.5 8.25l-7.5 7.5-7.5-7.5"
                        />
                      </svg>
                    </button>
                    <div id={`faq-answer-${index}`} class="hidden px-10 pb-5">
                      <p class="font-geist text-ink text-[14px] leading-[1.4] opacity-80">
                        {faq.a}
                      </p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                ))
              }
            </div>

            <script>
              document.querySelectorAll(".faq-toggle").forEach((button) => {
                button.addEventListener("click", () => {
                  const isExpanded =
                    button.getAttribute("aria-expanded") === "true";
                  button.setAttribute(
                    "aria-expanded",
                    (!isExpanded).toString()
                  );

                  const answerId = button.getAttribute("aria-controls");
                  if (answerId) {
                    const answer = document.getElementById(answerId);
                    if (answer) {
                      answer.classList.toggle("hidden");
                    }
                  }
                });
              });
            </script>
          </div>

          <!-- On Delivery/Pickup -->
          <div
            class="flex-1 bg-sky py-[80px] px-5 flex flex-col items-center gap-10"
          >
            <h2
              class="font-futura text-ink text-[40px] uppercase tracking-[-2px] leading-[0.92]"
            >
              on Delivery/Pickup
            </h2>
            <div
              class="w-full max-w-[512px] flex flex-col border-t border-ink"
              id="delivery-faq"
            >
              {
                [
                  {
                    q: "Do you provide plates/napkins and utensils?",
                    a: "Yes, we do! They are provided complimentary with your order.",
                  },
                  {
                    q: "Does The Taco Project do corporate catering?",
                    a: "Yes. Please contact our catering specialist, catering@thetacoproject.com.",
                  },
                  {
                    q: "Will my food be hot when I pick it up?",
                    a: "Yes. Your food will be fresh and hot when you pick it up and will be packed in foil pans to keep them warm.",
                  },
                  {
                    q: "Can I reheat or keep food hot in the oven?",
                    a: "Yes. You can keep your food hot or reheat it in the oven only. Our foil pans are non-microwavable.",
                  },
                  {
                    q: "Do you have staff that could help at my event?",
                    a: "Yes. We can provide Taco Project trained staff at an hourly rate of $30 with a 3 hour minimum. A 24 hour advance on hiring our staff is required.",
                  },
                  {
                    q: "Can my order be delivered?",
                    a: "Delivery from online catering orders will be provided via Uber and will be a direct drop off. Unboxing and setup will not be included by the driver.",
                  },
                  {
                    q: "Is there a fee for delivery?",
                    a: "Yes. It is $18.00",
                  },
                ].map((faq, index) => (
                  <div class="border-b border-ink">
                    <button
                      class="faq-toggle flex items-center justify-between gap-4 py-5 px-10 text-left w-full hover:bg-black/5 transition-colors cursor-pointer group"
                      aria-expanded="false"
                      aria-controls={`delivery-faq-answer-${index}`}
                    >
                      <span class="font-geist text-ink text-[16px] leading-[1.4]">
                        {faq.q}
                      </span>
                      <svg
                        xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                        fill="none"
                        viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                        stroke-width="1.5"
                        stroke="currentColor"
                        class="size-4 text-ink shrink-0 transition-transform duration-200 group-aria-expanded:rotate-180"
                      >
                        <path
                          stroke-linecap="round"
                          stroke-linejoin="round"
                          d="M19.5 8.25l-7.5 7.5-7.5-7.5"
                        />
                      </svg>
                    </button>
                    <div
                      id={`delivery-faq-answer-${index}`}
                      class="hidden px-10 pb-5"
                    >
                      <p class="font-geist text-ink text-[14px] leading-[1.4] opacity-80">
                        {faq.a}
                      </p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                ))
              }
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Testimonial -->
        <section class="bg-hot-sauce py-[100px] px-5">
          <div
            class="max-w-[760px] mx-auto flex flex-col items-start gap-[22px]"
          >
            <div class="flex gap-1">
              <!-- 5 Stars -->
              {
                [...Array(5)].map(() => (
                  <svg
                    xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                    viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                    fill="currentColor"
                    class="size-5 text-crema"
                  >
                    <path
                      fill-rule="evenodd"
                      d="M10.788 3.21c.448-1.077 1.976-1.077 2.424 0l2.082 5.007 5.404.433c1.164.093 1.636 1.545.749 2.305l-4.117 3.527 1.257 5.273c.271 1.136-.964 2.033-1.96 1.425L12 18.354 7.373 21.18c-.996.608-2.231-.29-1.96-1.425l1.257-5.273-4.117-3.527c-.887-.76-.415-2.212.749-2.305l5.404-.433 2.082-5.006z"
                      clip-rule="evenodd"
                    />
                  </svg>
                ))
              }
            </div>
            <p
              class="font-geist text-crema text-[24px] leading-[1.4] font-normal"
            >
              Had an amazing time at The Taco Project in Tarrytown! Everything
              was so good — from the Palomas and Mojitos to the Spicy Mango and
              Passion Fruit Margaritas. We loved the Buffalo Wings, Tuna
              Tostadas, and Nachos. The tacos were the best — Birria, El Pastor,
              and Shrimp, full of flavor. Finished with Flan and one of the best
              Tres Leches ever. Big thanks to Julian for being so friendly and
              helping us with the menu!
            </p>
            <p
              class="font-geist text-crema text-[14px] leading-[1.4] font-normal"
            >
              — Anju Kapoor
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- footer -->
        <footer id="footer" class="bg-ink">
          <!-- content wrapper with --max-content-width -->
          <div class="container">
            <!-- content wide logo -->
            <svg
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 1214 142"
              ><g fill="#dbd6c0" clip-path="url(#a)"
